8. Viability Theory with Fisher Information

8.1 Fisher-Refined Viability Kernel

K_F = \left\{ \Xi \in \mathcal{M} \mid E \ge E_{\min}, \; \Sigma \le \Sigma_{\max}, \; \det(g_{\mu\nu}) \ge \theta_{\min} \right\}

where g_{\mu\nu} is the Fisher Information Matrix. The condition \det(g) \ge \theta_{\min} ensures the system has sufficient self-awareness to navigate the thermodynamic landscape.

8.2 Hamilton-Jacobi-Isaacs (HJI) Game Formulation

Treat environmental perturbations as an adversary. The viability kernel is the zero sublevel set of the value function V(\Xi) solving:

\min_{u \in U} \max_{d \in D} \left[ \nabla V \cdot \dot{\Xi}(\Xi, u, d) \right] = 0

where u are control actions (throttling, cooling) and d are disturbances (load spikes, ambient temperature rises).

